Language: Ilocano
Language code: ilo
Lines: orth orth-seg gloss translat
Author: James Blackburn, Kazuki Shintani
Date: April 7, 2016
Source a: Rubino, Carl. Reference grammar of Ilocano. Diss. University of California, Santa Barbara, 1997.


######################################
######### WORD ORDER #################
######################################

# grammatically correct VS order with intransitive verb
Source: a:187
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {word order}
Naglaylay   ti      sabong
n-ag-laylay ti      sabong
PF-I-wilt   CORE.SG flower.ABS
`The flower wilted'

# grammatically incorrect VS order with intransitive verb
Source: a:187
Vetted: f
Judgment: u
Phenomena: {word order}
Ti      sabong     naglaylay
ti      sabong     n-ag-laylay
CORE.SG flower.ABS PF-I-wilt
`The flower wilted'

# correct article-to-noun order
Source: a:187
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {word order}
Naglaylay   ti      sabong
n-ag-laylay ti      sabong
PF-I-wilt   CORE.SG flower.ABS
`The flower wilted'

# incorrect article-to-noun order
Source: a:187
Vetted: s
Judgment: u
Phenomena: {word order}
Naglaylay   sabong     ti
n-ag-laylay sabong     ti
PF-I-wilt   flower.ABS CORE.SG
`The flower wilted'

# correct word order with transitive verb: tr CoreNP CoreNP
Source: a:32
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {word order}
Nakita   ti      babai ti      lalaki
na-kita  ti      babai ti      lalaki
PF.T-see CORE.SG girl  CORE.SG boy
`The girl saw the boy'

# incorrect word order with transitive verb: CoreNP tr CoreNP
Source: a:32
Vetted: s
Judgment: u
Phenomena: {word order}
Ti      babai nakita   ti      lalaki
ti      babai na-kita  ti      lalaki
CORE.SG girl  PF.T-see CORE.SG boy
`The girl saw the boy'

# incorrect word order with transitive verb: CoreNP CoreNP tr
Source: a:32
Vetted: s
Judgment: u
Phenomena: {word order}
Ti      babai ti      lalaki nakita
ti      babai ti      lalaki na-kita
CORE.SG girl  CORE.SG boy    PF.T-see
`The girl saw the boy'

# incorrect word order and case with transitive verb: oblique-NP tr oblique-NP
Source: a:32
Vetted: s
Judgment: u
Phenomena: {word order}
Iti    babai nakita   iti    lalaki
iti    babai na-kita  iti    lalaki
OBL.SG girl  PF.T-see OBL.SG boy
`The girl saw the boy'

# incorrect word order with transitive verb: oblique-NP oblique-NP tr
Source: a:32
Vetted: s
Judgment: u
Phenomena: {word order}
Iti    babai iti    lalaki nakita
iti    babai iti    lalaki na-kita
OBL.SG girl  OBL.SG boy    PF.T-see
`The girl saw the boy'

# incorrect det-noun order for NPs with transitive verb
Source: a:32
Vetted: s
Judgment: u
Phenomena: {word order}
Nakita   babai ti      ti      lalaki
na-kita  babai ti      ti      lalaki
PF.T-see girl  CORE.SG CORE.SG boy
`The girl saw the boy'

# incorrect det-noun order for NPs with transitive verb
Source: a:32
Vetted: s
Judgment: u
Phenomena: {word order}
Nakita   ti      babai lalaki ti
na-kita  ti      babai lalaki the
PF.T-see CORE.SG girl  boy    CORE.SG
`The girl saw the boy'

# incorrect det-noun order for NPs with transitive verb
Source: a:32
Vetted: s
Judgment: u
Phenomena: {word order}
Nakita   ti       babai  lalaki ti
na-kita  ti       babai  lalaki ti
PF.T-see CORE.SG  boy    girl   CORE.SG
`The girl saw the boy'

